StarTimes has added new flagship content to the delight of her subscribers. It added that it has also partnered Longrich to reward subscribers. The latest additions on StarTimes are top animation channel, DreamWorks, and premium football rights, La Liga. Under the deal, subscribers who visited StarTimes business halls to subscribe basic, smart, classic or super bouquets were given the company’s products. Content Marketing Manager, StarTimes Nigeria, Ali Auta, said the reward was to thank subscribers who have  stayed with the brand. He added that the new content is in line with the brand promise to make it a priority to broaden its content offering to meet varios interests without compromising affordability. “Despite the effect of the COVID-19 pandemic on family spending, many of our subscribers have kept on sacrificing other costs to keep enjoying the exciting entertainment that StarTimes brings to their homes. As a business, we find it worthy to celebrate them. We are proud to have partnered Longrich, widely known for its superior products, to delight our subscribers,” he said.